key_deliverables: BIM Execution Plan (BEP) outlining project standards, coordination processes, and deliverables.
Federated 3D Model (LOD 200) for interdisciplinary coordination and clash avoidance.
Architectural 3D Model (LOD 200) showing massing, vertical zoning, apartment layouts, 'fabric-first' envelope, and material placeholders (brick, timber).
Structural 3D Model (LOD 200) showing the primary frame (CLT/LGSF), floor slabs, and foundation concept.
MEP 3D Model (LOD 200) showing primary plant spaces, main service riser zones, and major equipment placeholders.
Conceptual Site Plan showing building footprint, access, and relationship to the urban context.
Ground Floor 'Plinth' Plan showing entrance lobby, secure bicycle storage, and central plant room.
Typical Upper Floor Plan illustrating the repeatable two-bedroom modular unit layout.
Roof Plan showing the layout of the extensive green roof, solar panel array, and rainwater collection system.
Key Building Elevations showing the proposed material aesthetic of brick and timber.
Key Building Sections illustrating the 'fabric-first' envelope, resilient plinth, and vertical zoning.
Preliminary Structural Framing Plans indicating the proposed prefabricated system.
Outline Architectural Specification defining performance criteria for the insulated envelope and the honest material palette.
Outline Structural Specification outlining requirements for geotechnical investigation, adjacent property surveys, fire engineering, and dynamic analysis of the lightweight structure.
Outline MEP Specification detailing regulatory compliance (UK Regs, London Plan), DfMA coordination requirements, and the scope for further TM59 and acoustic studies.
Sustainability & Resilience Strategy document detailing the approach to the green roof, solar generation, rainwater harvesting, and flood mitigation.
Preliminary Fire Strategy Report, with specific focus on the proposed prefabricated superstructure (CLT/LGSF).
Design for Manufacture and Assembly (DfMA) Strategy outlining the approach to prefabrication and modular coordination.

details: BIM/CAD documentation plan, refined 3D render, and simulated 3D plan generated.
